Estimated hours: Learning 6.5 hours, working and practicing 4 hours

Content Insights: Installing and configuring XAMMP for local host is free but a complicated process. Hosting service is an easier but costly option. I have found host gator to be affordable and has easy wordpress configuration and joomla features. Need to
explore Cpanel a bit more and get familiar with the interface.

Career/Employability/Learning Insights:
While working on the prac I realized my PHP knowledge is very limited. In order to cahnge and add new features on my site it is important to expand my experience with PHP. One of my favourite part of this language is that I can easily add PHP code in an HTML
code to customize and change content style/structures. I have also found lots of templates for Joomla online. I could use them and modify them to my needs to make my site look better. For future help:
